Sentencas: La1.6Sr0.4NiO4+delta-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathodes were prepared successfully using combustion synthesis method for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Properties and performance of La1.6Sr0.4NiO4+δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The chemical compatibility, thermal expansion behavior, electrical conductivity and electrode performance were studied.
Titulo: Properties and performance of La1.6Sr0.4NiO4+δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The X-ray diffraction of La1.6Sr0.4NiO4+delta-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite result proved a slight reaction between La1.6Sr0.4NiO4+delta and Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 Both the thermal expansion coefficient and the electrical conductivity of La1.6Sr0.4NiO4+delta-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 decreased with increasing Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 content.
Titulo: Properties and performance of La1.6Sr0.4NiO4+δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: AC impedance spectroscopy measurements indicated that the addition of 30 wt% Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 to La1.6Sr0.4NiO4+delta exhibited the lowest polarization resistance (0.238 Omega cm(2)) at 800 degrees C in air, which was only one fourth of the La1.6Sr0.4NiO4+delta electrode measured at the same temperature.
Titulo: Properties and performance of La1.6Sr0.4NiO4+δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
